Police are investigating Busia Governor Sospeter Ojaamong over allegations that he assaulted a medic after a disagreement in bar in Mumias town, Kakamega County.Western Region Police Commander Moses Ombati said the medic, Juma Khayombe, suffered a fracture in the left leg during a scuffle with the governor s aides at a hotel on Wednesday night.Mr Khayombe is said to have angered the governor when he spoke in support of the new Jubilee Party. At the moment investigations are still in progress on the matter and once we establish what happened, we shall come up with a decision on the next course of action, said Mr Ombati in Kakamega on Friday.The governor could not be reached for comment and was said to have travelled to Mombasa for ODM celebrations.The medic was being treated at St Mary s Mission Hospital in Mumias.Mr Khayombe said he had recorded a statement with the police. email print email print Peres will be buried next to Rabin, who was assassinated in 1995 by a Jewish extremist opposed to Ms Tutui said the court would have given orders for immediate realisation of the rule.